JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 102
IS  - 1
SP  - 147
EP  - 159
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - Implicit contracts are nontrivial Nash equilibria to the post-hiring trading game between a worker and the employer. These are supported by intrafirm, rather than labor market, reputations. The existence of an implicit contract that supports efficient trade is proved in a simple model.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1884685
